  "text": "The `runtime.Object` interface is defined in `staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/interfaces.go` (line 336) with two methods: `GetObjectKind() schema.ObjectKind` and `DeepCopyObject() Object`. Core/v1 API types in `staging/src/k8s.io/api/core/v1/types.go` implement this interface by embedding `metav1.TypeMeta` (which provides `GetObjectKind()` via `staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1/types.go`) and `metav1.ObjectMeta`. The `DeepCopyObject()` methods are generated in `zz_generated.deepcopy.go`. 45 types implement `runtime.Object` in core/v1 (Pod, PodList, Service, Node, Namespace, ConfigMap, Secret, etc.). These types are registered into the scheme via `staging/src/k8s.io/api/core/v1/register.go`, which uses `runtime.NewSchemeBuilder` (from `scheme_builder.go`) to create a `SchemeBuilder` that calls `addKnownTypes`, which in turn calls `scheme.AddKnownTypes()` (defined in `scheme.go` line 140) to register all 40+ core/v1 types under the GroupVersion `{Group: \"\", Version: \"v1\"}`.",
